00:12:57,344 --> 00:13:01,014
My one chance to impress Roxanne
and I blew it.

251
00:13:01,104 --> 00:13:02,474
Uh-huh!

252
00:13:02,564 --> 00:13:04,104
Max, look.

253
00:13:04,184 --> 00:13:07,274
It's the Leaning Tower of Cheese-a. Huh.

254
00:13:09,064 --> 00:13:10,154
(DOOR SQUEAKS OPEN)

255
00:13:11,194 --> 00:13:12,444
Oh, man.

256
00:13:12,524 --> 00:13:15,324
My dad is gonna smash me like a bug.

257
00:13:15,404 --> 00:13:18,824
Hey, P.J., detention! (LAUGHS)

258
00:13:18,904 --> 00:13:21,034
PRINCIPAL: Robert Zimuruski.

259
00:13:22,834 --> 00:13:24,794
Okay. I'm comin'.

260
00:13:24,874 --> 00:13:26,254
Max, here.

261
00:13:26,334 --> 00:13:28,464
Guard this with your life, dude.

262
00:13:34,464 --> 00:13:37,674
Hey, Maz-u-ur!

263
00:13:37,764 --> 00:13:39,684
What's up, bro? All right.

264
00:13:40,184 --> 00:13:42,184
Then my parents' air conditioner
went on the fritz.

265
00:13:42,264 --> 00:13:44,354
I figured with all those kids in my house,
the place'd be like a sauna.

266
00:13:44,434 --> 00:13:46,524
So I'm all freaked out,
but then I thought, like, use it.

267
00:13:46,604 --> 00:13:49,984
So my theme's gonna be,
"Powerline Goes Rain Forest."

268
00:13:50,064 --> 00:13:51,444
Too much?

269
00:13:51,524 --> 00:13:53,444
Roxanne, are you listening?

270
00:13:56,234 --> 00:13:58,194
Oh! (CLICKS TONGUE)

271
00:13:59,154 --> 00:14:01,824
-Stacey, no! I don't wanna...
-Talk to him.

272
00:14:02,574 --> 00:14:03,744
Ahem!

273
00:14:04,834 --> 00:14:06,994
A-A-Ahem! Hmm.

274
00:14:07,084 --> 00:14:08,204
Tap him.

275
00:14:10,414 --> 00:14:11,754
(GASPS)

276
00:14:21,014 --> 00:14:23,394
-Gosh, I'm sorry.
-It's okay... really.

277
00:14:27,314 --> 00:14:29,234
Um, I liked your dance.

278
00:14:29,314 --> 00:14:30,814
Yeah. (NERVOUS LAUGHTER)

279
00:14:30,894 --> 00:14:31,984
Yeah?

280
00:14:32,064 --> 00:14:34,024
Yeah, it's from Powerline's new video.

281
00:14:34,114 --> 00:14:36,234
I know. H-He's totally a genius.

282
00:14:36,324 --> 00:14:38,444
Yeah. He's doing a concert
next week in L.A.

283
00:14:38,534 --> 00:14:40,904
Oh, yeah.
Stacey's showing it at her party.

284
00:14:40,994 --> 00:14:42,704
-Yeah!
-Yeah.

285
00:14:45,244 --> 00:14:47,584
Um, uh, Roxanne...

286
00:14:47,664 --> 00:14:52,044
I was, uh, sorta, kinda
thinkin' that maybe I'd, um,

287
00:14:52,124 --> 00:14:56,594
ask you to, uh, go with me,
that is to the... party.

288
00:14:56,674 --> 00:14:58,714
Of course if you don't want to,
I'd completely understand.

289
00:14:58,804 --> 00:15:04,264
Well, I was sorta, kind of
thinkin' that... I'd love to.

290
00:15:04,344 --> 00:15:05,804
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

291
00:15:05,894 --> 00:15:07,144
-Good.
-Great.

292
00:15:07,224 --> 00:15:08,644
-Terrific.
-Wonderful.

293
00:15:08,724 --> 00:15:09,854
-All right.
-Okay.

294
00:15:09,934 --> 00:15:13,644
C'mon, Roxanne. We don't want
to belabor the moment now, do we?

295
00:15:13,734 --> 00:15:15,604
Well, I'd better be going.

296
00:15:15,694 --> 00:15:17,734
I'll, uh, call you later.

297
00:15:17,824 --> 00:15:19,024
Okay.

298
00:15:19,114 --> 00:15:20,404
Bye. Oh.

299
00:15:20,484 --> 00:15:23,324
(NERVOUS LAUGHTER) Bye.

300
00:15:24,614 --> 00:15:28,164
See, that wasn't so bad.
I told you men are easy to deal with.

301
00:15:28,244 --> 00:15:30,544
Yes! She said yes!

302
00:15:30,624 --> 00:15:32,664
Ya-ha-ha-hoo!

303
00:15:32,754 --> 00:15:37,674
Everybody mambo! Rum-bum-bum-bum-dah

304
00:15:37,754 --> 00:15:39,424
-Oooh!
-Rum-bum-bum-bum-dah

305
00:15:39,504 --> 00:15:42,214
It's not my break yet! Ooh!

306
00:15:42,304 --> 00:15:44,764
-Oooh!
-Rum-bum-bum-bum-dah

307
00:15:44,844 --> 00:15:48,394
Yeah! Dance with her! Groove with her.

308
00:15:48,474 --> 00:15:50,224
Rum-bum-bum-bum-dah

309
00:15:50,314 --> 00:15:52,064
-Miss Maple!
-Yes, sir?

310
00:15:52,144 --> 00:15:54,604
Get that boy's father
on the phone at once!

311
00:15:54,694 --> 00:15:56,904
Right away, sir! Whoo!

312
00:15:57,484 --> 00:15:58,444
Hello.

313
00:15:58,524 --> 00:16:00,774
Ah, yes. Mr. Goof.

314
00:16:00,864 --> 00:16:02,784
This is Principal Mazur.

315
00:16:02,864 --> 00:16:05,744
I'm calling in regard
to your son Maximilian.

316
00:16:05,824 --> 00:16:08,454
Max? Oh, my gosh! Is he hurt?

317
00:16:08,534 --> 00:16:09,954
No, Mr. Goof.

318
00:16:10,034 --> 00:16:11,334
He's in trouble!

319
00:16:11,414 --> 00:16:13,504
Trouble? What kind of trouble?

320
00:16:13,584 --> 00:16:15,834
-Dressed like a gang member...
-Gang member?

321
00:16:15,924 --> 00:16:18,834
your son caused the entire student body

322
00:16:18,924 --> 00:16:21,384
to break into a riotous frenzy!

323
00:16:21,464 --> 00:16:24,844
-Riot? Couldn't be my...
-If I were you, Mr. Goof,

324
00:16:24,924 --> 00:16:28,644
I'd seriously reevaluate the way
you're raising your child

325
00:16:28,724 --> 00:16:31,564
before he ends up in the electric chair!

326
00:16:31,644 --> 00:16:34,234
-(PHONE CLICKS DEAD)
-The electric chair?

327
00:16:35,894 --> 00:16:37,144
Oh!

328
00:16:37,904 --> 00:16:39,984
What am I gonna do?

329
00:16:41,484 --> 00:16:43,784
P.A. SYSTEM:
Blue light special on aisle three.

330
00:16:43,864 --> 00:16:47,034
P.A. SYSTEM:
Blue light special on aisle three.

331
00:17:05,464 --> 00:17:07,054
Lake Destiny.

332
00:17:07,844 --> 00:17:11,104
Okay, kiddo. Now, smile!

333
00:17:11,184 --> 00:17:13,014
Lake Destiny, Idaho!

334
00:17:13,104 --> 00:17:15,604
-Lake who-did-ho?
-You were right, Pete.

335
00:17:15,684 --> 00:17:17,434
Nothin' like the great outdoors

336
00:17:17,524 --> 00:17:19,904
to strengthen the bond
between father and son.

337
00:17:19,984 --> 00:17:21,814
-You said so yourself.
-Well, yeah, but...

338
00:17:21,904 --> 00:17:24,024
I'm goin' fishin'! Ayuk!

339
00:17:24,114 --> 00:17:26,494
I'm goin' fishin' with my boy!

340
00:17:27,154 --> 00:17:28,494
Yeah.

341
00:17:28,574 --> 00:17:31,574
Okay, precious, gimme a big smi...

342
00:17:31,664 --> 00:17:33,454
(GIRL LAUGHS)

343
00:17:33,534 --> 00:17:37,624
Fishing! Fishing! (LAUGHS)

344
00:17:37,714 --> 00:17:39,754
(SCHOOL BELL RINGS)

345
00:17:39,834 --> 00:17:42,174
-(KIDS CHEERING)
-Cool concert, lad.

346
00:17:42,254 --> 00:17:45,094
-What?
-You wailed, bud!

347
00:17:46,054 --> 00:17:49,684
-Hey, Max, wicked dance.
-Thanks.

348
00:17:49,764 --> 00:17:51,724
Forget it, girl. He's Roxanne's.

349
00:17:51,804 --> 00:17:53,434
Way to go, man!

350
00:17:53,514 --> 00:17:55,684
I just heard about you and Roxanne.

351
00:17:55,764 --> 00:17:57,934
Oh, Pete! Ow!

352
00:17:58,024 --> 00:18:01,524
See, see? I told you our plan would work!

353
00:18:01,604 --> 00:18:04,734
-Max! Max! Max!
-Peej, knock it off. Come on. Shh.

354
00:18:04,824 --> 00:18:08,614
-Maximum! Maxi-mu-um!
-Max! Max!

355
00:18:08,694 --> 00:18:12,534
Max! Max! Max! Max! Max!

356
00:18:12,614 --> 00:18:15,124
Max! Max! Max! Yeah!

357
00:18:15,204 --> 00:18:18,254
(SONG BEGINS) All I need is halfa chance
A second thought, a second glance

358
00:18:18,334 --> 00:18:22,004
To prove I've got whatever it takes

359
00:18:22,084 --> 00:18:23,754
It's a piece of cake.

360
00:18:23,834 --> 00:18:27,254
To stand out above the crowd

361
00:18:27,344 --> 00:18:29,974
Even if I gotta shout out loud

362
00:18:30,054 --> 00:18:32,764
'Til mine is the only face you'll see

363
00:18:32,844 --> 00:18:37,264
-Gonna stand out
-Stand out, heh

364
00:18:37,354 --> 00:18:38,894
Stand out

365
00:18:38,974 --> 00:18:40,774
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah

366
00:18:40,854 --> 00:18:41,854
Stand out

367
00:18:43,354 --> 00:18:46,864
'Til mine is the only face you'll see

368
00:18:46,944 --> 00:18:49,444
Gonna stand out

369
00:18:49,534 --> 00:18:50,784
'Til you notice me

370
00:18:52,574 --> 00:18:54,034
Goin' somewhere, Pop?

371
00:18:54,114 --> 00:18:58,044
-Sure are, pal-a-roony.
-Cool. Have a good time, Dad.

372
00:18:58,124 --> 00:19:00,504
If you're gonna be gone
more than a month, drop me a line.

373
00:19:00,584 --> 00:19:03,214
But, Max, this isn't just my vacation.

374
00:19:03,294 --> 00:19:06,294
It's a vacation with me and my best buddy.

375
00:19:06,384 --> 00:19:09,554
-Oh, Donald Duck?
-No, silly. With you!

376
00:19:14,014 --> 00:19:16,394
-(BIRDS TWITTERING)
-Are you okay, Maxie?

377
00:19:17,354 --> 00:19:18,604
Wh-What did you say?

378
00:19:18,684 --> 00:19:19,774
That's right!

379
00:19:19,854 --> 00:19:21,734
A vacation, son!

380
00:19:21,814 --> 00:19:25,194
We'll spend some
real quality time together!

381
00:19:25,274 --> 00:19:26,654
I think I'm gonna be sick.

382
00:19:26,734 --> 00:19:28,524
Hey, got a present for ya!

383
00:19:28,614 --> 00:19:30,904
Dad, stop that! What are you doing?

384
00:19:33,824 --> 00:19:36,494
You look just like I did at your age.

385
00:19:36,574 --> 00:19:38,124
Please don't say that, Dad.

386
00:19:38,204 --> 00:19:41,454
Wait! I saved the best for last. Ayuk!

387
00:19:42,624 --> 00:19:46,294
It's been handed down
from Goof to Goof to Goof.

388
00:19:46,384 --> 00:19:48,714
And now, it's yours, son.

389
00:19:48,794 --> 00:19:51,174
-A stick?
-No, silly.

390
00:19:51,264 --> 00:19:52,554
A fishin' pole!

391
00:19:53,264 --> 00:19:55,594
Fishing? We're going fishing?

392
00:19:55,684 --> 00:19:58,014
Yep. Just like my dad and me did.

393
00:19:58,104 --> 00:20:01,524
Two best buddies fishin' on Lake Destiny.

394
00:20:01,604 --> 00:20:03,524
Away from it all!

395
00:20:03,604 --> 00:20:06,354
I don't wanna be "away" from it all, Dad.

396
00:20:06,444 --> 00:20:08,114
I like "it all"!

397
00:20:08,194 --> 00:20:12,154
Look, Maxie, we're using
the same map me and my dad used.

398
00:20:12,234 --> 00:20:15,284
We'll take the same route,
and make the same stops...

399
00:20:15,364 --> 00:20:17,244
-and see the same sights.
-Ahh!

400
00:20:17,324 --> 00:20:20,704
-But that trip would take weeks, Dad!
-Exactly!

401
00:20:20,784 --> 00:20:22,704
Gettin' there is half the fun.

402
00:20:22,794 --> 00:20:24,004
Put the map away, Dad.

403
00:20:24,084 --> 00:20:27,174
-It's not gonna happen. I'm tellin' ya.
-Careful, son. You'll wrinkle my past.

404
00:20:27,254 --> 00:20:29,594
Ayuk! And our future.

405
00:20:29,674 --> 00:20:33,714
What the map says, Max, we will follow.

406
00:20:33,804 --> 00:20:36,304
That's very mystical and everything, Dad,

407
00:20:36,384 --> 00:20:39,344
but, uh, seriously, there's this party
I have to go to. And there's this girl...

408
00:20:39,434 --> 00:20:42,314
There'll be plenty of time
for parties when you're older.

409
00:20:42,394 --> 00:20:45,984
Why, when I was your age
I'd never even been invited to a party.

410
00:20:46,064 --> 00:20:48,944
-Look at me now!
-Great, Dad.

411
00:20:49,524 --> 00:20:51,404
-Hop in, Maxie.
-No.

412
00:20:54,864 --> 00:20:56,574
All right, then.

413
00:20:56,654 --> 00:20:58,614
Guess I'll just have to go...

414
00:20:58,704 --> 00:21:00,164
all alone.

415
00:21:00,244 --> 00:21:01,954
That's all.

416
00:21:02,034 --> 00:21:06,374
Just sit in the boat all alone...

417
00:21:06,464 --> 00:21:08,294
and talk to myself.

418
00:21:09,174 --> 00:21:11,844
-All alone.
-I guess so.

419
00:21:11,924 --> 00:21:14,174
-Oh, come on! Hop in!
-No, Dad.

420
00:21:14,254 --> 00:21:16,554
-Just hop right in there.
-No.

421
00:21:16,634 --> 00:21:19,684
-Come on, Maxie. Go for it!
-Argh! No.

422
00:21:20,764 --> 00:21:22,304
Let's buckle you up!

423
00:21:22,394 --> 00:21:24,524
And we're ready for takeoff! Ayuk.

424
00:21:27,524 --> 00:21:28,774
Set for adventure, Maxie?

425
00:21:28,854 --> 00:21:31,484
Why are you doing this to me, Dad?

426
00:21:31,564 --> 00:21:35,864
'Cause I don't want ya
to end up in the electric chair.

427
00:21:35,944 --> 00:21:37,194
Electric chair? What are you...

428
00:21:37,284 --> 00:21:39,204
I'm not givin' up on ya, son.

429
00:21:39,284 --> 00:21:41,954
Together, we're gonna work this out.

430
00:21:42,034 --> 00:21:43,374
Work this out? But, Dad!

431
00:21:43,454 --> 00:21:45,414
No buts about it, Maxie boy.

432
00:21:45,494 --> 00:21:47,584
-Your ol' pop knows best.
-But...

433
00:21:47,664 --> 00:21:50,254
(CAR ENGINE REVVING)

434
00:21:51,924 --> 00:21:55,174
Goodbye, house. Goodbye, mailbox.

435
00:21:55,254 --> 00:21:56,844
(TIRES SCREECHING)

436
00:21:56,924 --> 00:21:58,844
Goodbye, pile of broken wood.

437
00:22:01,514 --> 00:22:02,804
Goodbye, hopes.

438
00:22:02,894 --> 00:22:04,304
Goodbye, dreams.

439
00:22:04,394 --> 00:22:05,814
Goodbye, Roxanne.

440
00:22:06,434 --> 00:22:07,434
Roxanne!

441
00:22:07,524 --> 00:22:10,314
Dad, I gotta stop somewhere first.
I have to talk to someone.

442
00:22:10,394 --> 00:22:11,854
-Well...
-Turn here!

443
00:22:11,944 --> 00:22:13,234
(CAR SCREECHES)

444
00:22:13,314 --> 00:22:16,824
-D-Dad, watch out! Aaah!
-(YELLING)

445
00:22:16,904 --> 00:22:18,494
Stop here. Here! Pull over!

446
00:22:20,244 --> 00:22:22,034
Now, make it quick, Maxie boy.

447
00:22:22,114 --> 00:22:24,124
We gotta put some road behind us.

448
00:22:25,534 --> 00:22:28,374
You get and cancel your first date
in less than an hour.

449
00:22:29,874 --> 00:22:31,964
-(DOORBELL RINGS)
-Must be some kind of lame-o record.

450
00:22:32,044 --> 00:22:33,214
(DOOR OPENS)

451
00:22:34,174 --> 00:22:36,174
(GROWLS)

452
00:22:36,844 --> 00:22:39,174
Hi. Is Roxanne home?

453
00:22:39,264 --> 00:22:40,724
(GROWLS)

454
00:22:40,804 --> 00:22:44,054
-M-M-My name's Max.
-(GROWLS)

455
00:22:44,144 --> 00:22:46,974
Does Roxanne live here?

456
00:22:47,064 --> 00:22:49,984
-Does she even live on this block? Ha-ha.
-ROXANNE: Wait!

457
00:22:50,064 --> 00:22:52,314
It's okay, Daddy.
Max is a friend from school.

458
00:22:52,894 --> 00:22:54,614
Oh. (GROWLS)

459
00:22:54,694 --> 00:22:57,484
Go on. Go on. Good Daddy.

460
00:22:58,574 --> 00:23:00,694
-Hey, Max.
-Hi, there.

461
00:23:01,574 --> 00:23:04,034
You wanna... uh, have a seat?

462
00:23:04,114 --> 00:23:06,874
Hey. Uh... oh.

463
00:23:09,374 --> 00:23:10,794
-(GROWLS)
-Daddy!

464
00:23:11,754 --> 00:23:14,714
I promise, he'll be better behaved
when you pick me up for the party.

465
00:23:14,794 --> 00:23:17,844
Yeah, that's, uh, sorta why I came by.

466
00:23:17,924 --> 00:23:19,964
I'm really looking forward to it, Max.

467
00:23:20,054 --> 00:23:23,884
-Yeah. I was too.
-Was?

468
00:23:23,974 --> 00:23:26,894
You see, my dad's
on this stupid father-son kick and...

469
00:23:26,974 --> 00:23:29,684
Don't worry about it, Max.
It's just a dumb party.

470
00:23:29,774 --> 00:23:32,604
No, it's not. Roxanne,
I really wanted to go with you.

471
00:23:32,684 --> 00:23:35,314
-Max, I understand. Really, it's okay.
-But my dad surprised me.

472
00:23:35,404 --> 00:23:37,154
I don't wanna go, but I have no choice.

473
00:23:37,234 --> 00:23:38,524
I'm sure I can find someone else.

474
00:23:39,654 --> 00:23:40,984
Someone else?

475
00:23:41,074 --> 00:23:44,864
-I'll just talk to you later.
-Uh, uh, Roxanne!

476
00:23:44,954 --> 00:23:46,954
Uh, my dad is, uh...

477
00:23:47,034 --> 00:23:49,284
My dad's taking me
to the Powerline concert in L.A.

478
00:23:50,204 --> 00:23:54,374
Your dad's taking you clear across
the country just to see a concert?

479
00:23:54,964 --> 00:23:57,544
Uh, well, you see, uh, my dad...

480
00:23:57,634 --> 00:24:00,424
uh, knew... knows... knows Powerline.

481
00:24:00,504 --> 00:24:02,464
They used to play together, in a band!

482
00:24:02,554 --> 00:24:05,764
-Yeah!
-(CAR HORN TOOTS) Come on, son!

483
00:24:05,844 --> 00:24:07,514
Let's get this show on the road!

484
00:24:07,594 --> 00:24:09,474
Uh... (NERVOUS LAUGHTER) Just a minute!

485
00:24:09,554 --> 00:24:12,854
You... party animal, you.

486
00:24:15,854 --> 00:24:18,944
-You're really serious.
-Absolutely.

487
00:24:19,984 --> 00:24:21,364
So, uh...

488
00:24:21,444 --> 00:24:24,614
you aren't still thinkin'
of goin' with someone else, are you?

489
00:24:24,704 --> 00:24:27,744
-Well, I guess...
-Because I was hopin'...

490
00:24:27,824 --> 00:24:30,494
I could, uh, wave to you onstage

491
00:24:30,584 --> 00:24:33,204
when we join Powerline
for the final number.

492
00:24:33,294 --> 00:24:34,754
This is incredible.

493
00:24:35,334 --> 00:24:36,834
Well, I wouldn't miss
our date for anything

494
00:24:36,924 --> 00:24:38,464
that wasn't incredible, Roxanne.

495
00:24:39,584 --> 00:24:40,544
Mwa.

496
00:24:43,094 --> 00:24:44,924
Have a great time at the concert, Max.

497
00:24:45,014 --> 00:24:47,724
-(MUMBLING)
-I'll see you on TV!

498
00:24:47,804 --> 00:24:50,764
Ah. I'm in deep sludge.

499
00:24:50,854 --> 00:24:53,064
(CAR ENGINE REVVING)

500
00:25:00,064 --> 00:25:01,444
GOOFY: Day one.

501
00:25:01,524 --> 00:25:03,194
Well, here we are,

502
00:25:03,284 --> 00:25:06,864
out on the open road,
retracin' the steps of my boyhood.

503
00:25:06,954 --> 00:25:10,374
And here's Maxie! Ayuk!

504
00:25:10,454 --> 00:25:12,244
Say hi, Max.

505
00:25:13,204 --> 00:25:16,464
-Well, how 'bout a wave?
-Not now, Dad.

506
00:25:16,544 --> 00:25:18,374
Ayuk! What a kidder!

507
00:25:22,794 --> 00:25:23,964
Hmm.

508
00:25:27,724 --> 00:25:30,144
Fun games I used to play with my dad.

509
00:25:30,224 --> 00:25:34,264
Road bingo. Twenty ques...
(GASPS) Hey, Maxie.

510
00:25:34,354 --> 00:25:35,524
Let's play a game.

511
00:25:35,604 --> 00:25:38,314
You think of a name,
and I'll try and guess who it is.

512
00:25:38,394 --> 00:25:40,984
-Uh, man or woman?
-Oh, man.

513
00:25:41,064 --> 00:25:42,314
A man, huh?

514
00:25:42,404 --> 00:25:44,574
Hmm, that's a toughie.

515
00:25:44,654 --> 00:25:46,074
Uh, let's see.

516
00:25:47,324 --> 00:25:49,154
-Walt Disney!
-Right.

517
00:25:49,244 --> 00:25:50,784
I'm good at this.

518
00:25:50,864 --> 00:25:52,494
Now, uh, I'll think of one.

519
00:25:52,574 --> 00:25:54,954
-Hmm.
-(ROCK MUSIC BLARING ON RADIO)

520
00:25:56,954 --> 00:25:59,924
Oh! You wanna sing a song, huh?

521
00:26:00,004 --> 00:26:03,594
Me and my dad used to sing this one
all the time.

522
00:26:04,294 --> 00:26:06,214
-(SONG BEGINS)
-High hopes

523
00:26:06,304 --> 00:26:09,474
GOOFY: (SINGING) He's got high hopes

524
00:26:09,554 --> 00:26:12,974
He's got high apple pie

525
00:26:13,054 --> 00:26:15,474
In the sky hopes

526
00:26:15,564 --> 00:26:19,394
(HARD ROCK PLAYS)

527
00:26:19,894 --> 00:26:22,234
-(ROCK STOPS)
-Oops, there goes another...

528
00:26:22,314 --> 00:26:25,154
(HARD ROCK PLAYS)

529
00:26:25,734 --> 00:26:27,614
-(ROCK STOPS)
-Oops, there goes...

530
00:26:27,694 --> 00:26:30,244
-(HARD ROCK)
-Oops, there goes...

531
00:26:30,324 --> 00:26:33,414
-(HARD ROCK)
-Oops...

532
00:26:34,074 --> 00:26:36,034
(CASSETTE TAPE WHIRS AND SCRATCHES)

533
00:26:38,754 --> 00:26:41,834
Oh, g-great, Dad.
Now we don't have any music!

534
00:26:41,924 --> 00:26:44,504
Oh, Maxie. It's not so bad.

535
00:26:44,584 --> 00:26:46,714
We'll just have to entertain ourselves!

536
00:26:47,844 --> 00:26:49,384
(DEEP SIGH)

537
00:26:49,464 --> 00:26:52,224
(PERSISTENT JINGLING SOUND)

538
00:26:53,894 --> 00:26:56,054
(JINGLING CONTINUES)

539
00:26:57,104 --> 00:26:58,934
(KEYS JINGLING)

540
00:26:59,604 --> 00:27:00,684
(EXHAUST PIPE SPUTTERS, POPS)

541
00:27:00,774 --> 00:27:02,774
Putt-putt-poof!

542
00:27:02,854 --> 00:27:05,114
Putt-putt-poof!

543
00:27:05,194 --> 00:27:07,324
-Ping-ping-ping.
-Putt-putt-poof!

544
00:27:07,404 --> 00:27:11,324
-Ping-ping-ping. Ping-ping-ping.
-(JOLLY WHISTLING)

545
00:27:11,404 --> 00:27:13,664
-Ping-ping-ping.
-Putt-putt-poof.

546
00:27:13,744 --> 00:27:16,954
-Ping-ping-ping.
-Putt-putt-poof.

547
00:27:17,034 --> 00:27:18,494
(SONG BEGINS)

548
00:27:20,794 --> 00:27:25,334
(SINGS) Do ya need a break
from modern livin'?

549
00:27:25,424 --> 00:27:29,254
Do you long to shed your weary load?

550
00:27:29,844 --> 00:27:32,094
If your nerves are raw
And your brain is fried

551
00:27:32,174 --> 00:27:35,474
Just grab a friend
And take a ride together

552
00:27:35,554 --> 00:27:38,394
-On the open road
-(TIRES SCREECHING)

553
00:27:38,474 --> 00:27:40,524
Come on, Maxie! Ayuk!

554
00:27:40,604 --> 00:27:44,774
All in all, I'd rather have detention

555
00:27:44,854 --> 00:27:48,114
All in all, I'd rather eat a toad

556
00:27:48,194 --> 00:27:49,904
-Yuck!
-(HORNS HONKING)

557
00:27:49,984 --> 00:27:51,904
Old man drives like such a klutz

558
00:27:51,994 --> 00:27:55,034
That I'm about to hurl my guts directly...

559
00:27:55,114 --> 00:27:58,284
Upon the open road

560
00:27:58,374 --> 00:28:00,624
GOOFY: There's nothin' can upset me

561
00:28:00,704 --> 00:28:02,794
'Cause now we're on our way

562
00:28:02,874 --> 00:28:06,674
Our trusty map will guide us
Straight and true

563
00:28:07,294 --> 00:28:09,174
Roxanne, please don't forget me

564
00:28:09,254 --> 00:28:10,804
I will return someday

565
00:28:10,884 --> 00:28:14,724
-(YELLS)
-Though I may be in traction when I do

566
00:28:15,804 --> 00:28:19,224
-Me and Max relaxin' like the old days
-This is worse...

567
00:28:19,304 --> 00:28:22,314
-... Than dragon breath and acne
-In a buddy-buddy kind of way

568
00:28:22,394 --> 00:28:25,144
I'm so mad I think I may explode

569
00:28:25,234 --> 00:28:29,194
-When I see that highway I could cry
-That's funny, so could I

570
00:28:29,274 --> 00:28:32,864
(BOTH SINGING TOGETHER)
Just bein' out on the open road

571
00:28:33,824 --> 00:28:37,784
(PIANO MUSIC PLAYING)

572
00:28:39,784 --> 00:28:41,284
Howdy, boys

573
00:28:41,374 --> 00:28:43,624
Is this the way to Nashville?

574
00:28:43,704 --> 00:28:45,464
-(TRUCK HONKS)
-Watch it, Mac!

575
00:28:45,544 --> 00:28:48,884
Or you'll be gettin' towed

576
00:28:48,964 --> 00:28:51,174
I'm in no hurry to arrive

577
00:28:51,254 --> 00:28:53,554
'Cause I'll be turnin' sixty-five

578
00:28:53,634 --> 00:28:56,974
The next time I sees the open road

579
00:28:59,724 --> 00:29:04,104
-Just a week of rest and relaxation
-Yeah!

580
00:29:04,184 --> 00:29:07,234
And the odd romantic episode

581
00:29:07,314 --> 00:29:08,944
Very odd!

582
00:29:09,024 --> 00:29:11,064
And it's Califor-ni-a or bust

583
00:29:11,154 --> 00:29:13,194
Look out, you dirt-bags, eat my dust

584
00:29:13,274 --> 00:29:17,574
From now on, I own the open road

585
00:29:17,654 --> 00:29:19,744
It's me and little Maxie

586
00:29:19,824 --> 00:29:21,914
My pip-squeak pioneer

587
00:29:21,994 --> 00:29:25,164
They're partners forever, westward ho

588
00:29:25,254 --> 00:29:26,334
-Yee-haw!
-Yee-haw!

589
00:29:26,414 --> 00:29:30,714
Could someone call a taxi
And get me outta here?

590
00:29:30,794 --> 00:29:34,254
To Beverly Hills 90210

591
00:29:34,344 --> 00:29:38,554
Oh, every day, another new adventure

592
00:29:39,264 --> 00:29:43,564
Every mile, another new ZIP Code

593
00:29:44,144 --> 00:29:46,314
And the cares we had are gone for good

594
00:29:46,394 --> 00:29:48,444
And I'd go with them if I could

595
00:29:48,524 --> 00:29:50,814
I got no strings on me

596
00:29:50,904 --> 00:29:52,864
I'm feelin' fancy free

597
00:29:52,944 --> 00:29:56,074
How wonderful to be

598
00:29:56,154 --> 00:30:00,994
On the open ro-oad

599
00:30:01,074 --> 00:30:04,534
Ro-oad

600
00:30:05,954 --> 00:30:07,374
(CLANGING SOUND)

601
00:30:13,134 --> 00:30:16,384
(GOOFY SINGING)

602
00:30:16,464 --> 00:30:20,434
You'll all do-do-do-do

603
00:30:21,264 --> 00:30:23,514
-Do-do-do bum-bum-bum
-(TRUCK HORN BLOWS)

604
00:30:23,604 --> 00:30:24,854
GOOFY: Grandpa! Grandpa!

605
00:30:24,934 --> 00:30:26,434
-(HORN BLARES)
-(MAX YELLS)

606
00:30:28,184 --> 00:30:31,394
-(GOOFY HUMS)
-Dad, you're gonna get us killed!

607
00:30:31,484 --> 00:30:34,614
-Why don't you just give me the map?
-Oh, no thanks, son.

608
00:30:34,694 --> 00:30:36,944
Navigating's a big responsibility.

609
00:30:37,034 --> 00:30:40,864
Besides, you wouldn't wanna
spoil the big surprise!

610
00:30:40,954 --> 00:30:44,074
I'm takin' you someplace pretty special.

611
00:30:51,164 --> 00:30:54,294
Gosh! It's even better than I remembered.

612
00:30:54,384 --> 00:30:57,964
No, Mommy! I don't wanna go! (SOBBING)

613
00:30:58,054 --> 00:31:00,134
Yeah, fun. Tell you what...

614
00:31:00,224 --> 00:31:02,474
-I'm just gonna wait here in the car.
-Ayuk!

615
00:31:02,554 --> 00:31:04,644
You party pooper! Come on.

616
00:31:04,724 --> 00:31:06,434
This is gonna be fun!

617
00:31:07,014 --> 00:31:09,354
Oh, howdy there, folks.

618
00:31:09,434 --> 00:31:12,484
Lester's is proud to present

619
00:31:12,564 --> 00:31:16,524
the Possum Posse Jamboree.

620
00:31:17,154 --> 00:31:18,154
Here it is.

621
00:31:18,234 --> 00:31:20,364
(CROWD CHEERS)

622
00:31:20,444 --> 00:31:22,954
Oh, boy! Just in time.

623
00:31:24,534 --> 00:31:26,664
(FIDDLE MUSIC PLAYS)

624
00:31:28,334 --> 00:31:30,084
Howdy, folks.

625
00:31:30,164 --> 00:31:32,834
Who's your favorite possum?

626
00:31:32,914 --> 00:31:34,464
Lester!

627
00:31:34,544 --> 00:31:36,844
(KIDS LAUGH AND CLAP)

628
00:31:36,924 --> 00:31:38,804
Got us a seat right up front.

629
00:31:38,884 --> 00:31:41,344
LESTER: Let me introduce you to the posse.

630
00:31:41,424 --> 00:31:44,804
Here's Beuford, Beulah, and Mordachai.

631
00:31:44,884 --> 00:31:46,594
(ELECTRONIC SCREECHING)

632
00:31:46,684 --> 00:31:50,434
Hey, Lester, ready for yodelin'? Ha-ha-ha.

633
00:31:50,524 --> 00:31:52,274
Sure am, Beuford!

634
00:31:52,354 --> 00:31:54,194
(SINGS) Now gather 'round my possum pals

635
00:31:54,274 --> 00:31:55,564
Join the jamboree

636
00:31:55,654 --> 00:31:58,234
Come hoot and howl
And holler from the heart...

637
00:31:59,024 --> 00:32:00,784
This is pathetic.

638
00:32:02,244 --> 00:32:06,574
-Here in Lester's Possum Park
-LESTER: Join in, folks.

639
00:32:06,664 --> 00:32:08,994
This is yodelin' time!

640
00:32:09,084 --> 00:32:12,334
Yodel-lay-ee, yodel-ee-oo

641
00:32:12,414 --> 00:32:14,294
Yodel-ee-oo, ooo-ooo-ooo

642
00:32:14,374 --> 00:32:16,964
Lester's Possum Park

643
00:32:18,504 --> 00:32:21,174
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah

644
00:32:21,254 --> 00:32:23,384
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah

645
00:32:23,464 --> 00:32:26,634
Ayuk! Yodel-lay-ee, ooo-ooo-ooo

646
00:32:26,724 --> 00:32:28,434
-LESTER: Don't you wanna be
-ALL: Mm-hmm.

647
00:32:28,514 --> 00:32:29,854
-A-hangin' from a tree?
-ALL: Uh-huh.

648
00:32:29,934 --> 00:32:34,774
We're mighty glad to see ya
And the parking's always free

649
00:32:34,854 --> 00:32:38,404
Here at Lester's Po-Po

650
00:32:38,484 --> 00:32:42,114
Po-Possum Park

651
00:32:42,194 --> 00:32:44,534
Doodle-do, diddle-do

652
00:32:44,614 --> 00:32:46,824
(CROWD LAUGHS)

653
00:32:48,284 --> 00:32:50,284
Hey, that's the ticket!

654
00:32:50,374 --> 00:32:53,164
I'll be right back, my little possum pal.

655
00:32:53,244 --> 00:32:55,334
(SIGHS) My life's a living...

656
00:32:55,414 --> 00:32:57,624
Hello, little buddy!

657
00:32:59,504 --> 00:33:02,344
Who's your favorite possum?

658
00:33:02,924 --> 00:33:04,424
Don't touch me.

659
00:33:04,514 --> 00:33:07,974
Aww. Why such a long face?

660
00:33:08,054 --> 00:33:10,854
You're so sad. (CRIES)

661
00:33:10,934 --> 00:33:14,064
I know! You need a big hug from Lester.

662
00:33:14,144 --> 00:33:16,564
-Don't even think about it! No!
-See?

663
00:33:16,644 --> 00:33:19,854
Now you feel all good inside.

664
00:33:20,564 --> 00:33:21,814
Beat it, doofus!

665
00:33:23,984 --> 00:33:26,784
(CHILDREN CHATTERING)

666
00:33:26,864 --> 00:33:30,574
-Oh, no. No, Dad. Not that. Please.
-Here you go, sport.

667
00:33:30,664 --> 00:33:32,704
What say we get our picture taken?

668
00:33:32,784 --> 00:33:35,584
(WAILING)

669
00:33:35,664 --> 00:33:38,924
-You have got to be kidding.
-Oh, all right.

670
00:33:39,004 --> 00:33:40,504
But you're missin' out.

671
00:33:41,584 --> 00:33:44,344
-Urgh. Huh?
-(CROWD LAUGHS)

672
00:33:44,424 --> 00:33:46,384
Hiya, son!

673
00:33:46,464 --> 00:33:48,384
(CROWD HOWLS WITH LAUGHTER)

674
00:33:48,474 --> 00:33:50,974
Hey, everyone! Check out the dork!

675
00:33:51,054 --> 00:33:52,474
Say "sassafras."

676
00:33:52,554 --> 00:33:54,974
Sassy-frass!

677
00:33:55,064 --> 00:33:58,564
-(POSSUM SCREECHES)
-Argh!

678
00:33:58,644 --> 00:34:00,774
-(CROWD LAUGHS)
-Ahh! Get it! Get it!

679
00:34:00,854 --> 00:34:04,574
(BANJO MUSIC STARTS UP)

680
00:34:04,654 --> 00:34:07,244
That's the spirit, Maxie!

681
00:34:09,204 --> 00:34:10,574
Whoa! No!

682
00:34:10,664 --> 00:34:13,244
Dad, stop! Please! No!

683
00:34:14,244 --> 00:34:15,664
Dad, look, this is embarrassing.

684
00:34:15,744 --> 00:34:17,954
No, no, no!

685
00:34:18,044 --> 00:34:20,164
Let go! Dad!

686
00:34:20,254 --> 00:34:22,214
-Ta-da! Ayuk.
-(APPLAUSE)

687
00:34:22,294 --> 00:34:24,134
(CROWD SIGHS)

688
00:34:24,214 --> 00:34:28,134
It's Dork and Dork Junior! Hah-hah-hah!

689
00:34:28,214 --> 00:34:31,224
(CROWD HOWLS WITH LAUGHTER)

690
00:34:35,054 --> 00:34:37,854
(THUNDERCLAPS)

691
00:34:41,104 --> 00:34:43,024
(EXASPERATED GRUNTING)

692
00:34:49,864 --> 00:34:51,534
-Argh!
-Max!

693
00:34:52,824 --> 00:34:54,874
Hey, what the heck you tryin' to do?

694
00:34:54,954 --> 00:34:57,954
-Trying to get away from you!
-Me?

695
00:34:58,704 --> 00:35:01,334
-What'd I do?
-Forget it!

696
00:35:01,414 --> 00:35:04,754
I thought we was having fun.
What's the matter?

697
00:35:04,834 --> 00:35:06,214
Nothin'. Let's just go.

698
00:35:07,214 --> 00:35:08,384
Well, come on!

699
00:35:10,514 --> 00:35:12,134
(JINGLING OF CAR KEYS)

700
00:35:16,554 --> 00:35:18,104
(SLAMS DOOR)

701
00:35:20,064 --> 00:35:21,934
Hey, you dropped your hat.

702
00:35:22,024 --> 00:35:24,854
Ah! This is the stupidest vacation!

703
00:35:24,944 --> 00:35:27,574
You drag me from home,
you jam me in this dumb car,

704
00:35:27,654 --> 00:35:31,324
then drive me a million miles away
to see some stupid rat show!

705
00:35:32,114 --> 00:35:33,704
Call me when the trip's over.

706
00:35:34,574 --> 00:35:36,664
(THUNDERCLAPS)

707
00:35:38,624 --> 00:35:39,874
(CAR ENGINE REVS UP)

708
00:35:57,354 --> 00:35:59,854
(HAMMERING)

709
00:36:21,664 --> 00:36:23,164
Hey, Max.

710
00:36:23,254 --> 00:36:26,374
You wanna get in some fishin' practice?

711
00:36:26,464 --> 00:36:29,464
Just a couple of days
'til we get to Lake Destiny.

712
00:36:30,804 --> 00:36:32,004
Maybe later.

713
00:36:40,934 --> 00:36:41,934
(SPLASH)

714
00:36:46,484 --> 00:36:48,904
(RUMBLING)

715
00:36:53,994 --> 00:36:54,944
(SAWING)

716
00:37:07,624 --> 00:37:09,004
Whoa!

717
00:37:09,084 --> 00:37:11,094
Now that's camping.

718
00:37:11,174 --> 00:37:13,924
Did you say somethin', Max? Ow!

719
00:37:19,594 --> 00:37:21,684
-Pete?
-Goofy?

720
00:37:21,764 --> 00:37:25,814
Oh-ho! What a serendipity doo-dah!

721
00:37:25,894 --> 00:37:28,194
Who'd've thunk it, huh? (LAUGHS)

722
00:37:28,274 --> 00:37:31,234
-Is P.J. here?
-Who? Oh, yeah.

723
00:37:31,314 --> 00:37:33,694
I'm sure he's loafin'
around here somewhere.

724
00:37:33,774 --> 00:37:35,654
-(SONG PLAYING)
-It ain't a question of how

725
00:37:35,744 --> 00:37:37,904
Just a matter of when

726
00:37:37,994 --> 00:37:40,954
You get the message
That I'm trying to sing

727
00:37:41,034 --> 00:37:44,244
I'm under a spell, I'm in over my head

728
00:37:44,334 --> 00:37:47,504
And you know I'm goin'
All of the way to the end

729
00:37:47,584 --> 00:37:48,874
What a goob!

730
00:37:48,964 --> 00:37:52,674
-To stand out above the crowd
-(SONG STOPS)

731
00:37:52,754 --> 00:37:55,424
(CONTINUES SINGING)
Even if you got to shout out loud

732
00:37:55,514 --> 00:37:58,134
No matter what the look is
It's Max, I get...

733
00:37:58,224 --> 00:37:59,344
-Max!
-H-H-Hey!

734
00:37:59,434 --> 00:38:01,844
Whoa! Small wilderness, dude.

735
00:38:01,934 --> 00:38:04,644
-Didn't expect to run into you.
-Apparently not.

736
00:38:04,724 --> 00:38:08,354
You're just jealous, man,
'cause you ain't got the moves!

737
00:38:08,434 --> 00:38:10,104
MAX: Yeah, you can keep the moves.

738
00:38:10,194 --> 00:38:14,024
But I wouldn't mind havin' this RV. Oh!

739
00:38:14,114 --> 00:38:18,494
-You are so lucky, man.
-Me? Oh, come on. You're the star.

740
00:38:18,574 --> 00:38:21,364
-Wh-What do you...
-Going to the Powerline concert.

741
00:38:21,454 --> 00:38:25,284
-Ah! It's unbelievable, man.
-Who told you about that?

742
00:38:25,374 --> 00:38:28,124
Hey, come on. Everybody in town
knows about it, Max.

743
00:38:28,204 --> 00:38:30,834
You are gonna be famous, buddy.

744
00:38:30,924 --> 00:38:33,294
Especially with Roxanne.

745
00:38:34,294 --> 00:38:38,264
There's, uh, only one person
who doesn't know about it yet, Peej.

746
00:38:38,344 --> 00:38:40,764
-Who?
-My dad.

747
00:38:41,344 --> 00:38:42,764
So tell me, Goof.

748
00:38:42,844 --> 00:38:45,354
Is that kid of yours
still givin' you guff?

749
00:38:45,434 --> 00:38:46,934
Oh, I don't know what's wrong.

750
00:38:47,014 --> 00:38:50,854
Just seems like everything I try
only drives Max further away.

751
00:38:51,734 --> 00:38:54,024
Maybe I oughta just back off,
I don't know.

752
00:38:54,114 --> 00:38:56,404
Wrong, Goof. (SIGHS)

753
00:38:56,484 --> 00:38:59,074
Look, if you keep 'em under your thumb,

754
00:38:59,154 --> 00:39:02,074
they'll never end up in the gutter.

755
00:39:08,084 --> 00:39:10,334
Too bad, Pete. Almost.

756
00:39:10,414 --> 00:39:12,214
Almost? Hah!

757
00:39:12,294 --> 00:39:13,714
Watch this.

758
00:39:13,794 --> 00:39:15,424
P.J.!

759
00:39:15,504 --> 00:39:18,054
(P.J. PANTS)
Here, sir. Comin', sir. Yes, sir.

760
00:39:23,134 --> 00:39:25,094
Whoo-hoo! Strike-ola!

761
00:39:25,184 --> 00:39:27,604
Yee-haw! Thank you. Thank you. Yes!

762
00:39:27,684 --> 00:39:30,184
And the crowd goes wild! Ahh-ha-ha-ha!

763
00:39:30,274 --> 00:39:31,434
High five, son!

764
00:39:31,524 --> 00:39:35,024
Psych! Ha-ha-ha-ha!

765
00:39:35,104 --> 00:39:37,944
Say, Goof, why don't
you two stay for dinner?

766
00:39:38,024 --> 00:39:40,324
-Cool!
-Oh, no thanks, Pete.

767
00:39:40,404 --> 00:39:43,784
-Max and I have some fish to catch.
-Dad, we can do that tomorrow.

768
00:39:43,864 --> 00:39:45,534
So, uh, what're we havin'?

769
00:39:45,624 --> 00:39:49,664
-But, Max, I thought...
-Ahem! Under your thumb, Goof.

770
00:39:52,124 --> 00:39:53,464
-Maximilian!
-What?

771
00:39:53,544 --> 00:39:55,294
Get your gear, little man.

772
00:39:55,374 --> 00:39:57,174
We're goin' fishin'!

773
00:39:58,884 --> 00:40:00,924
And I mean now!

774
00:40:01,014 --> 00:40:02,094
(SIGHS)

775
00:40:09,854 --> 00:40:11,774
Dad, I don't even know how to fish.

776
00:40:11,854 --> 00:40:14,234
Oh, now come on. That never stopped me!

777
00:40:14,314 --> 00:40:16,064
Let me show you a little family secret,

778
00:40:16,154 --> 00:40:19,904
handed down through
about 12 or 13 Goof generations.

779
00:40:19,984 --> 00:40:22,654
The perfect cast!

780
00:40:22,744 --> 00:40:24,324
The perfect what?

781
00:40:24,404 --> 00:40:25,864
The perfect cast.

782
00:40:25,954 --> 00:40:28,534
My dad taught it to me
when I was about your age.

783
00:40:29,124 --> 00:40:31,294
Okay now, watch carefully.

784
00:40:31,914 --> 00:40:34,164
You gotta be I-I-loose.

785
00:40:34,254 --> 00:40:37,384
Relaxed, with your feet apart.

786
00:40:37,464 --> 00:40:40,964
And... ten o'clock, two o'clock...

787
00:40:41,054 --> 00:40:43,514
Quarter to three, tour jeté.

788
00:40:43,594 --> 00:40:45,764
Twist, over, pas de deux.

789
00:40:45,844 --> 00:40:48,724
I'm a little teapot and the windup!

790
00:40:51,104 --> 00:40:51,934
Huh?

791
00:40:52,014 --> 00:40:53,644
And let her fly!

792
00:40:54,774 --> 00:40:56,894
The perfect cast.

793
00:40:58,154 --> 00:40:59,154
(THUD)

794
00:41:00,564 --> 00:41:03,574
(RUMBLING FOOTSTEPS)

795
00:41:03,654 --> 00:41:06,114
(DEEP GROWLS)

796
00:41:07,864 --> 00:41:11,084
Huh? (SNIFFS, GROWLS)

797
00:41:11,164 --> 00:41:13,794
And now we reel her in.

798
00:41:16,334 --> 00:41:19,254
Grrr. Ah! Ooh!

799
00:41:19,884 --> 00:41:22,004
Oof! Grrr!

800
00:41:22,634 --> 00:41:24,094
(GROWLS)

801
00:41:26,724 --> 00:41:29,014
-Whoa!
-Grrr!

802
00:41:29,974 --> 00:41:31,434
Quick, get the camera!

803
00:41:32,934 --> 00:41:34,314
(GURGLING)

804
00:41:36,604 --> 00:41:38,854
Must be over three pounds.

805
00:41:38,944 --> 00:41:40,524
I don't wanna miss this!

806
00:41:43,404 --> 00:41:44,734
Look, Max!

807
00:41:44,824 --> 00:41:46,824
A... duh, D-Dad?

808
00:41:46,904 --> 00:41:49,204
It's Bigfoot!

809
00:41:49,284 --> 00:41:52,914
Could you back up a bit, Mr. Foot?
You're out of focus.

810
00:41:52,994 --> 00:41:54,494
(ROARS)

811
00:41:56,124 --> 00:41:57,414
-What's the idea?
-(GROWLING)

812
00:41:57,504 --> 00:41:59,294
-(YELLING)
-(ROARING)

813
00:41:59,374 --> 00:42:00,714
Bigfoot!

814
00:42:05,504 --> 00:42:08,014
Behold the legendary Bigfoot!

815
00:42:08,094 --> 00:42:11,224
Fabled, but seldom... Yeow-hoo-hoo!

816
00:42:12,804 --> 00:42:14,724
-It's locked!
-Quick! The sunroof!

817
00:42:14,814 --> 00:42:16,814
(BIGFOOT SNARLS)

818
00:42:17,314 --> 00:42:18,314
Hurry up!

819
00:42:18,394 --> 00:42:21,064
(SNARLS)

820
00:42:21,154 --> 00:42:22,734
Hurry up!

821
00:42:25,864 --> 00:42:27,194
Huh?

822
00:42:27,284 --> 00:42:28,364
MAX: Whoa!

823
00:42:30,494 --> 00:42:32,204
I can't believe it!

824
00:42:32,824 --> 00:42:34,124
Bigfoot!

825
00:42:34,204 --> 00:42:36,704
And I got the only video!

826
00:42:36,794 --> 00:42:39,164
We're gonna be famous!

827
00:42:39,254 --> 00:42:40,544
(HAPPY GROWLS)

828
00:42:41,124 --> 00:42:43,464
Huh? Grrr.

829
00:42:44,634 --> 00:42:46,174
Let's just get outta here.

830
00:42:49,054 --> 00:42:51,804
(KEYS JINGLING)

831
00:42:52,894 --> 00:42:54,764
Ha-ha!

832
00:42:57,934 --> 00:42:59,984
(SNIFFS) Ooh.

833
00:43:03,354 --> 00:43:04,774
(CHUCKLES)

834
00:43:10,114 --> 00:43:11,614
Is he gone yet?

835
00:43:13,034 --> 00:43:14,824
Mm-mm-mm-mm?

836
00:43:14,914 --> 00:43:17,834
-Nnn. Bb-fftt.
-Bb-bbb-bbb.

837
00:43:17,914 --> 00:43:19,914
(SNARLING, GROWLING)

838
00:43:20,004 --> 00:43:21,834
Ha-ha-ha-ha!

839
00:43:23,004 --> 00:43:25,294
Nope. He's still here.

840
00:43:25,384 --> 00:43:27,254
Ha-ha-ha-ha!

841
00:43:30,674 --> 00:43:31,924
(GROWLING)

842
00:43:32,014 --> 00:43:35,344
Gee, Max, was that Bigfoot
or your stomach?

843
00:43:35,434 --> 00:43:37,104
Man, I'm starving.

844
00:43:38,724 --> 00:43:41,814
Ayuk! Alphabet Soup comin' up.

845
00:43:43,194 --> 00:43:44,654
(DOOR SQUEAKS OPEN)

846
00:43:44,734 --> 00:43:45,864
Huh?

847
00:43:47,064 --> 00:43:48,574
-(GROWLS)
-Uh, Dad?

848
00:43:48,654 --> 00:43:50,074
(GROWLING CONTINUES)

849
00:43:50,154 --> 00:43:51,194
Dad!

850
00:43:52,364 --> 00:43:54,994
Stop playing around! He's coming!

851
00:43:59,454 --> 00:44:04,334
-(MUSIC PLAYS THROUGH EARPHONES)
-(BIGFOOT MUTTERS)

852
00:44:05,374 --> 00:44:09,174
You can tell by the way
I use my walk I'm a woman's man

853
00:44:09,254 --> 00:44:10,634
No time to talk

854
00:44:10,714 --> 00:44:12,724
(BIGFOOT CHUCKLES)

855
00:44:12,804 --> 00:44:14,974
I've been kicked around since I was born

856
00:44:15,054 --> 00:44:17,304
But then it's all right, it's okay

857
00:44:18,974 --> 00:44:21,474
Well, it's nice to know
this thing's good for somethin'.

858
00:44:23,434 --> 00:44:25,944
(MUFFLED MUSIC PLAYS IN BACKGROUND)

859
00:44:26,024 --> 00:44:30,484
(PLAYS OVER RADIO) Ah, ah, ah, ah
Stayin' alive, stayin' alive

860
00:44:30,574 --> 00:44:33,494
Ah, ah, ah, ah, stayin' alive...

861
00:44:38,284 --> 00:44:41,454
(LAUGHS)

862
00:44:41,544 --> 00:44:43,294
What's so funny?

863
00:44:44,414 --> 00:44:45,624
"Hi, Dad" Soup.

864
00:44:45,714 --> 00:44:47,084
Huh?

865
00:44:47,174 --> 00:44:49,844
Don't tell me you don't remember
"Hi, Dad" Soup!

866
00:44:51,134 --> 00:44:53,304
Oh, come on. Sure you do.

867
00:44:53,384 --> 00:44:57,264
You used to spell things out
using the letters, like, uh, "Hi, Dad,"

868
00:44:57,344 --> 00:44:59,224
-Or Maxie, or...
-Ambidextrous?

869
00:44:59,304 --> 00:45:01,064
Yeah! That's... Huh?

870
00:45:01,144 --> 00:45:03,354
No! Little words like...

871
00:45:03,434 --> 00:45:05,854
-Hasta la vista?
-Like "Bye-bye. "

872
00:45:05,944 --> 00:45:09,564
-Or "I pledge allegiance"...
-Ayuk-ayuk. Or "I love you. "

873
00:45:14,404 --> 00:45:17,074
Is, uh... is it soup yet?

874
00:45:17,154 --> 00:45:18,864
Oh, oh. I almost forgot.

875
00:45:20,324 --> 00:45:22,334
Whoa! Where'd you learn to do that?

876
00:45:22,914 --> 00:45:25,834
Your granddad taught me that
when we went to Yosemite.

877
00:45:26,544 --> 00:45:28,374
You two did a lot together, huh?

878
00:45:28,464 --> 00:45:29,884
Yep.

879
00:45:31,544 --> 00:45:33,384
-Max, you and I...
-Dad, I'm sorry...

880
00:45:34,134 --> 00:45:37,634
Um, um... how's the soup?

881
00:45:38,684 --> 00:45:40,724
Not bad. Um, not... Ahem.

882
00:45:43,104 --> 00:45:45,684
-What?
-N-nothin'.

883
00:45:45,774 --> 00:45:48,854
(BIGFOOT SNARLS AND GRUNTS)

884
00:45:53,444 --> 00:45:56,444
Well, we might as well get some shuteye.

885
00:45:56,534 --> 00:45:58,574
I don't think
we're goin' anywhere tonight.

886
00:46:19,884 --> 00:46:21,184
Hi, Maxie.

887
00:46:23,304 --> 00:46:27,434
(BIGFOOT GROANS, SUCK THUMB)

888
00:46:27,524 --> 00:46:30,484
(SNORING)

889
00:46:32,404 --> 00:46:34,904
(LOUD SNORING)

890
00:46:36,824 --> 00:46:38,694
(SNORING)

891
00:46:44,454 --> 00:46:47,624
(SNORING CONTINUES)

892
00:46:58,804 --> 00:47:00,844
"Dear Roxanne,

893
00:47:00,924 --> 00:47:02,344
I couldn't sleep...

894
00:47:03,304 --> 00:47:05,514
so I thought I'd drop you a line.

895
00:47:06,144 --> 00:47:09,434
Dad and I are having a great time!
We're only days away from L.A.

896
00:47:09,524 --> 00:47:12,604
and I can hardly wait
for the big concert."

897
00:47:13,984 --> 00:47:15,314
(GOOFY YAWNS)

898
00:47:16,154 --> 00:47:18,444
More "Hi, Dad" Soup, please.

899
00:47:22,994 --> 00:47:24,164
(SIGHS)

900
00:47:25,454 --> 00:47:28,914
"Dear Roxanne, sorry I lied,

901
00:47:28,994 --> 00:47:31,714
but I'm not really going
to the Powerline concert.

902
00:47:31,794 --> 00:47:33,924
You may never want to see me again..."

903
00:47:35,334 --> 00:47:36,594
Oh, man.

904
00:47:37,384 --> 00:47:39,424
I'm dead no matter what I do!

905
00:48:10,244 --> 00:48:12,874
(SNORING CONTINUES)

906
00:48:23,054 --> 00:48:24,554
(PENCIL SNAPS)

907
00:48:28,604 --> 00:48:31,184
(GOOFY YAWNS)

908
00:48:37,194 --> 00:48:40,524
How many cups of sugar
does it take to get to the moon?

909
00:48:41,114 --> 00:48:44,324
Ah... three and a half?

910
00:48:45,954 --> 00:48:47,284
(GOOFY SNORES)

911
00:49:08,304 --> 00:49:12,474
(COUNTRY AND WESTERN MUSIC PLAYS)

912
00:49:15,524 --> 00:49:16,944
(BELL RINGS)

913
00:49:18,064 --> 00:49:20,404
-Pickup!
-Hold your horses.

914
00:49:25,694 --> 00:49:27,284
-Short stack?
-Right here.

915
00:49:27,364 --> 00:49:29,164
Here you go, hun. Eggs?

916
00:49:30,124 --> 00:49:31,244
Eggs?

917
00:49:31,334 --> 00:49:33,664
-Eggs!
-Oh, yeah, yeah. Right here. Sorry.

918
00:49:33,744 --> 00:49:35,504
Here you go, cutie.

919
00:49:53,314 --> 00:49:57,274
-Max, I think we need to talk about this.
-Huh?

920
00:49:57,354 --> 00:50:01,024
Seems to me you need to start
taking some responsibility around here.

921
00:50:02,114 --> 00:50:05,364
Excuse me.
Can I have your attention, please?

922
00:50:05,444 --> 00:50:06,784
(GOOFY CLEARS THROAT)

923
00:50:06,864 --> 00:50:11,164
I, Goofy, hereby dub my son Maximilian...

924
00:50:11,244 --> 00:50:16,584
Official Navigator and Head "Which-Wayer"
of this here road trip.

925
00:50:16,664 --> 00:50:19,214
-Isn't that nice?
-Hee-haw!

926
00:50:19,294 --> 00:50:20,874
Seriously?

927
00:50:20,964 --> 00:50:23,634
GOOFY: I'm not even lookin'
at the map any more.

928
00:50:23,714 --> 00:50:27,514
As a matter of fact, you can pick all
the stops from here to Lake Destiny.

929
00:50:28,264 --> 00:50:30,184
I trust you wholeheartedly, son.

930
00:50:31,474 --> 00:50:33,264
To the open road!

931
00:50:34,854 --> 00:50:36,604
To the... open road!

932
00:50:43,614 --> 00:50:47,444
Wha-hoo! Wha-hoo!

933
00:50:52,494 --> 00:50:53,494
(TIRE BURSTS)

934
00:50:54,784 --> 00:50:55,914
-Ooh!
-Ow!

935
00:50:58,254 --> 00:51:01,254
-Ya-hoo!
-Woo-hoo!

936
00:51:01,334 --> 00:51:03,714
-(MAX CHEERS)
-(GOOFY GULPS)

937
00:51:12,684 --> 00:51:14,344
(CROWD CHEERS)

938
00:51:21,354 --> 00:51:22,644
Oh boy!

939
00:51:38,584 --> 00:51:39,914
(BOTH WHISTLE)

940
00:51:43,464 --> 00:51:46,084
-(MAX GRUNTS)
-Whoa!

941
00:51:52,054 --> 00:51:53,474
(CAMERA CLICKS)

942
00:51:53,554 --> 00:51:54,934
(BATS SQUEAKING)

943
00:51:55,014 --> 00:51:56,554
(MAX AND GOOFY SCREAM)

944
00:51:58,394 --> 00:52:01,564
-(CROWD CHEERS)
-Oo-oo-waah!

945
00:52:04,814 --> 00:52:07,774
-Wah-ha-hoo!
-Oof!

946
00:52:17,204 --> 00:52:18,374
(CRASHING)

947
00:52:24,414 --> 00:52:25,754
Gosh!

948
00:52:27,294 --> 00:52:28,714
MAX: Whoa-ho-ho!

949
00:52:28,794 --> 00:52:32,344
-Check out the bed!
-(WATER SLOSHING)

950
00:52:32,424 --> 00:52:33,924
Check out the dresser!

951
00:52:34,014 --> 00:52:35,184
Coral!

952
00:52:35,844 --> 00:52:36,974
Nice lamp.

953
00:52:38,304 --> 00:52:40,764
-Classy choice there, Navigator.
-(POUNDING ON DOOR)

954
00:52:40,854 --> 00:52:42,274
-MALE VOICE: This is the police!
-Huh?

955
00:52:42,354 --> 00:52:46,444
We've got the place surrounded, see?
You Goofs come out with your hands up.

956
00:52:46,524 --> 00:52:48,064
(IMITATING MACHINE GUN FIRE)

957
00:52:48,154 --> 00:52:50,074
(LAUGHS)

958
00:52:50,154 --> 00:52:52,574
You should've seen the look on your face!

959
00:52:52,654 --> 00:52:53,494
(PETE LAUGHS)

960
00:52:53,574 --> 00:52:56,744
-Ayuk! You really had him fooled, Pete!
-Me?

961
00:52:56,824 --> 00:52:58,704
You jumped outta your skin!

962
00:52:58,784 --> 00:53:01,624
-I was just pretendin' for your sake.
-All right, sure!

963
00:53:01,704 --> 00:53:03,914
-GOOFY: Did too!
-MAX: Did not!

964
00:53:04,004 --> 00:53:05,664
Oh, ain't this sweet?

965
00:53:05,754 --> 00:53:07,254
(PETE LAUGHS)

966
00:53:07,334 --> 00:53:10,384
Don't let him fool you
with that buddy-buddy act now.

967
00:53:10,464 --> 00:53:12,754
Under your thumb!

968
00:53:12,844 --> 00:53:17,014
So... since we're all
bein' palsy-walsy here,

969
00:53:17,094 --> 00:53:19,264
-how 'bout lettin' me hook up the RV?
-Well...

970
00:53:19,344 --> 00:53:22,604
Oh, it's just a tiny extension cord.
You'll hardly even notice it.

971
00:53:22,684 --> 00:53:25,024
-Okay.
-Great! P.J.!

972
00:53:25,104 --> 00:53:27,694
(P.J. GRUNTS)

973
00:53:30,484 --> 00:53:33,784
Hey, Goof, why don't you order us a pizza?
This might take a while.

974
00:53:37,654 --> 00:53:39,994
-No, I mean it... Ahh!
-Here you go, kids.

975
00:53:40,074 --> 00:53:41,834
I'm gonna check out the hot tub.

976
00:53:41,914 --> 00:53:43,834
-Okay, sir.
-All right.

977
00:53:43,914 --> 00:53:45,754
I can't believe you, man.

978
00:53:45,834 --> 00:53:49,124
Whatever made you think your dad
would fall for a stupid idea like that?

979
00:53:49,214 --> 00:53:52,004
-It wasn't stupid!
-Come on! It was really stupid.

980
00:53:52,094 --> 00:53:53,884
P.J.: Changing the map?

981
00:53:53,964 --> 00:53:57,974
MAX: I didn't know what I was doin',
all right? I-I was panicked.

982
00:53:58,054 --> 00:53:59,974
(HOT TUB BUBBLING)

983
00:54:01,724 --> 00:54:03,474
Oof-oof-oof.

984
00:54:03,564 --> 00:54:05,434
Oh-oh-ah-ah!

985
00:54:06,274 --> 00:54:08,734
Ah!

986
00:54:15,614 --> 00:54:19,244
Taking a break from
the MTV generation, huh?

987
00:54:19,324 --> 00:54:20,614
Can't say I blame ya.

988
00:54:21,324 --> 00:54:22,784
(SPLASH)

989
00:54:22,874 --> 00:54:24,914
People are always puttin'
too much water in these things.

990
00:54:26,084 --> 00:54:27,294
So, um...

991
00:54:27,374 --> 00:54:31,214
you and your son seem to be, uh,
gettin' along just hunky-dory, huh?

992
00:54:31,294 --> 00:54:33,504
Yeah, it's been great!

993
00:54:33,594 --> 00:54:36,304
You know, it's funny, but none
of your techniques worked for me.

994
00:54:37,054 --> 00:54:39,134
The harder I tried, the worse it got.

995
00:54:39,224 --> 00:54:43,264
-Once I eased up, things just clicked!
-Oh, that's swell.

996
00:54:43,354 --> 00:54:46,604
So, there's no problems then, huh?

997
00:54:46,684 --> 00:54:48,604
Not a one!

998
00:54:50,734 --> 00:54:53,024
That's, uh... (SIGHS)

999
00:54:53,104 --> 00:54:56,324
I just hate to be the bearer
of bad news, but uh...

1000
00:54:56,944 --> 00:54:58,074
What is it, Pete?

1001
00:54:58,784 --> 00:55:02,414
-Your kid's dupin' ya.
-What do you mean?

1002
00:55:02,494 --> 00:55:05,624
Well, I heard the little mutant tellin'
P.J. that he changed the map,

1003
00:55:05,704 --> 00:55:08,504
so you're headin' straight to L.A., pal.

1004
00:55:09,294 --> 00:55:12,044
-What?
-Oh, you tried, Goof.

1005
00:55:12,124 --> 00:55:14,464
He's just a bad kid, that's all.

1006
00:55:15,344 --> 00:55:16,594
I don't believe you.

1007
00:55:17,174 --> 00:55:19,714
-What?
-I don't believe ya, Pete!

1008
00:55:19,804 --> 00:55:23,134
Well, hey, don't take my word for it.
Check your map.

1009
00:55:23,224 --> 00:55:25,184
I don't need to check the map.

1010
00:55:25,264 --> 00:55:26,644
I trust my son.

1011
00:55:28,184 --> 00:55:32,064
You know, maybe Max isn't all the things
that you think a son should be.

1012
00:55:32,144 --> 00:55:34,444
But... he loves me.

1013
00:55:34,524 --> 00:55:36,984
Hey, my son respects me!

1014
00:55:37,944 --> 00:55:39,034
Yeah.

1015
00:55:41,114 --> 00:55:43,034
Check the map, Goof!

1016
00:55:53,794 --> 00:55:56,084
(CAR DOOR OPENS)

1017
00:56:18,734 --> 00:56:19,734
Hi, Dad.

1018
00:56:22,324 --> 00:56:24,654
Sorry about the mess. I-I'll clean it up.

1019
00:56:28,494 --> 00:56:29,994
(WATER SLOSHES)

1020
00:56:36,334 --> 00:56:39,094
-Me think I better go.
-See ya, Peej.

1021
00:56:39,634 --> 00:56:42,384
-P.J.: Don't forget... Powerline!
-MAX: Shh!

1022
00:57:19,544 --> 00:57:21,594
Well, here you go, Navigator.

1023
00:57:23,004 --> 00:57:25,974
Just follow my route on the map, son.

1024
00:57:27,554 --> 00:57:28,974
Okay.

1025
00:57:29,684 --> 00:57:31,604
Um, huh...

1026
00:57:32,974 --> 00:57:34,354
Here comes our junction.

1027
00:57:38,404 --> 00:57:41,114
Okay, Max, now this is it. Left or right?

1028
00:57:41,194 --> 00:57:42,824
Uh...

1029
00:57:45,194 --> 00:57:46,864
Come on, Max!

1030
00:57:46,954 --> 00:57:48,074
Uh, left!

1031
00:57:57,414 --> 00:57:58,924
(SIGH OF RELIEF)

1032
00:58:02,254 --> 00:58:04,674
Uh... how 'bout a song, Dad?

1033
00:58:06,634 --> 00:58:08,134
Uh... a game?

1034
00:58:08,224 --> 00:58:10,264
A game. Yeah! Yeah, a game. Okay.

1035
00:58:10,344 --> 00:58:11,974
Uh... a man or woman?

1036
00:58:13,724 --> 00:58:16,184
A man? Man, okay. Uh... Walt Disney!

1037
00:58:16,274 --> 00:58:18,734
(CAR SCREECHES TO A HALT)

1038
00:58:19,354 --> 00:58:20,734
(GOOFY GRUNTS)

1039
00:58:30,494 --> 00:58:31,664
(SIGHS)

1040
00:58:41,794 --> 00:58:42,794
Dad...

1041
00:58:43,464 --> 00:58:45,554
Listen, about my directions...

1042
00:58:45,634 --> 00:58:48,634
Will you listen to me?
I gotta tell you somethin', Dad.

1043
00:58:48,724 --> 00:58:52,514
Why bother? I'm probably too stupid
to understand anyway.

1044
00:58:52,594 --> 00:58:53,684
Right?

1045
00:58:54,434 --> 00:58:56,104
Ah, forget it.

1046
00:59:11,704 --> 00:59:13,204
H-H-Hey, the car!

1047
00:59:13,284 --> 00:59:15,954
-What? Now you want to drive, too?
-No, Dad.

1048
00:59:16,034 --> 00:59:17,704
The car! Look!

1049
00:59:17,794 --> 00:59:19,414
The car!

1050
00:59:20,914 --> 00:59:22,084
(METAL SCREECHING)

1051
00:59:23,584 --> 00:59:24,834
What'd you do now, Max?

1052
00:59:24,924 --> 00:59:26,924
I didn't do anything, Dad.
I only touched it.

1053
00:59:29,134 --> 00:59:31,594
W-W-Whoa!

1054
00:59:36,814 --> 00:59:38,314
You locked it!

1055
00:59:38,394 --> 00:59:41,484
I locked it? It's your door.
You locked it.

1056
00:59:41,564 --> 00:59:43,144
Well, you distracted me.

1057
00:59:43,234 --> 00:59:44,524
Whoa!

1058
00:59:44,604 --> 00:59:47,154
-You should've put the brake on.
-(METAL SCREECHING)

1059
00:59:47,234 --> 00:59:48,904
Why don't you just put it on yourself?

1060
00:59:50,074 --> 00:59:52,494
See? You ruin everything.

1061
00:59:52,574 --> 00:59:54,414
(CLANKING)

1062
00:59:54,494 --> 00:59:57,834
W-well, y-you r-ruined the vacation.

1063
00:59:57,914 --> 01:00:00,504
-MAX: I ruined it?
-(CRASHING)

1064
01:00:00,584 --> 01:00:03,334
-(CRASHING CONTINUES)
-I never... wanted to go...

1065
01:00:03,414 --> 01:00:04,874
on this stupid...

1066
01:00:04,964 --> 01:00:08,424
vacation!

1067
01:00:17,354 --> 01:00:18,854
Ah! Ah!

1068
01:00:18,934 --> 01:00:22,024
-Now look where you've got us, Dad!
-Where I got us?

1069
01:00:22,104 --> 01:00:24,524
-You should've let me stay at home.
-Why?

1070
01:00:25,144 --> 01:00:26,774
So you'd end up in prison?

1071
01:00:26,864 --> 01:00:29,274
Prison? What are you talkin' about?

1072
01:00:30,154 --> 01:00:33,074
-Your principal called me.
-It's not what you think.

1073
01:00:33,154 --> 01:00:35,324
-You even lied to me!
-(CRASH)

1074
01:00:35,414 --> 01:00:37,624
I had to! You were ruining my life.

1075
01:00:37,704 --> 01:00:41,204
I was only tryin'
to take my boy fishin', okay?

1076
01:00:41,294 --> 01:00:43,834
I'm not your little boy any more, Dad!

1077
01:00:43,914 --> 01:00:45,504
I've grown up.

1078
01:00:45,584 --> 01:00:47,254
I've got my own life now.

1079
01:00:47,334 --> 01:00:48,964
I know that!

1080
01:00:49,044 --> 01:00:51,304
I just wanted to be part of it.

1081
01:00:54,424 --> 01:00:56,264
You're my son, Max.

1082
01:00:56,344 --> 01:00:58,554
No matter how big you get,

1083
01:00:58,644 --> 01:01:00,764
you'll always be my son.

1084
01:01:21,954 --> 01:01:23,084
(SPLASH)

1085
01:01:45,644 --> 01:01:47,484
(SONG BEGINS)

1086
01:01:50,314 --> 01:01:54,324
MAX: (SINGS) There are times you drive me
Shall we say, bananas

1087
01:01:54,984 --> 01:01:58,664
And your mind is missin'
No offense, a screw

1088
01:01:58,744 --> 01:01:59,994
None taken.

1089
01:02:00,074 --> 01:02:02,494
Still, whatever mess I land in

1090
01:02:02,584 --> 01:02:05,334
Who is always understandin'?

1091
01:02:05,414 --> 01:02:08,874
Nobody else but you

1092
01:02:09,834 --> 01:02:13,964
Oh, your moodiness is
Now and then bewilderin'

1093
01:02:14,964 --> 01:02:18,174
And your values may be, so to speak, askew

1094
01:02:18,264 --> 01:02:19,554
-Gesundheit.
-Thanks.

1095
01:02:19,634 --> 01:02:22,474
Who deserves a hero's trophy

1096
01:02:22,554 --> 01:02:24,764
As we face each catastro-phee?

1097
01:02:24,854 --> 01:02:28,854
Nobody else but you

1098
01:02:30,144 --> 01:02:34,524
MAX AND GOOFY: (SINGING)
Nobody else but you

1099
01:02:34,614 --> 01:02:36,534
It's just our luck

1100
01:02:37,114 --> 01:02:39,824
We're stuck together

1101
01:02:39,904 --> 01:02:44,244
Nobody else but you

1102
01:02:44,334 --> 01:02:49,664
It's crazy enough to believe
We'll come through

1103
01:02:51,294 --> 01:02:55,254
So your jokes are all
Let's face it, prehistoric

1104
01:02:56,464 --> 01:02:59,844
And your music sounds
Like monkeys in a zoo

1105
01:03:01,344 --> 01:03:04,054
But when life becomes distressin'

1106
01:03:04,144 --> 01:03:06,224
Who will I be SOS-in'?

1107
01:03:06,314 --> 01:03:08,604
If you're havin' trouble guessing

1108
01:03:08,684 --> 01:03:10,944
Here's a clue

1109
01:03:11,024 --> 01:03:13,564
Though he seems intoxicated

1110
01:03:13,654 --> 01:03:16,194
He's just highly animated

1111
01:03:16,274 --> 01:03:19,114
And he's nobody else but

1112
01:03:19,194 --> 01:03:23,034
Nobody else but you

1113
01:03:23,744 --> 01:03:25,834
We've turned into

1114
01:03:25,914 --> 01:03:28,874
A true-blue duo

1115
01:03:28,954 --> 01:03:33,214
Hard times, we've had a few

1116
01:03:33,294 --> 01:03:35,464
Like we're thrown in the drink

1117
01:03:35,544 --> 01:03:37,884
Like we're tossed out of town

1118
01:03:37,964 --> 01:03:40,344
But when I start to sink

1119
01:03:40,424 --> 01:03:43,224
Hey, I'd rather go down

1120
01:03:43,304 --> 01:03:45,304
With nobody else

1121
01:03:45,394 --> 01:03:50,814
But Y-O-U

1122
01:03:50,894 --> 01:03:52,604
-(KISSES)
-Aw, Dad!

1123
01:03:52,694 --> 01:03:53,904
(SONG ENDS)

1124
01:03:56,564 --> 01:04:00,034
MAX: Anyway, I figure she's never
gonna want to talk to me again,

1125
01:04:00,114 --> 01:04:01,654
much less go out with me.

1126
01:04:02,494 --> 01:04:05,244
-What a dumb lie, huh?
-What do you know?

1127
01:04:05,324 --> 01:04:08,284
My Maxie... in love.

1128
01:04:08,874 --> 01:04:10,834
Gosh, you're really growin' up.

1129
01:04:10,914 --> 01:04:15,174
It happened so fast...
I guess I sort of missed it.

1130
01:04:16,754 --> 01:04:19,714
Well, I think the only thing
for us to do now

1131
01:04:19,804 --> 01:04:22,304
is to get you up onstage
with this Powerline feller.

1132
01:04:22,384 --> 01:04:25,594
(MAX CHUCKLES)
Uh, how are we gonna do that?

1133
01:04:25,684 --> 01:04:28,974
-Well, you just leave that up to me.
-No, Dad, really,

1134
01:04:29,064 --> 01:04:31,184
I-I think we should just,
you know, forget it.

1135
01:04:31,274 --> 01:04:35,144
Now how come you always think I'm gonna
lead you into some sort of calamity?

1136
01:04:35,234 --> 01:04:36,854
Uh, uh, Dad? Dad?

1137
01:04:36,944 --> 01:04:39,524
-What's wrong now?
-Look!

1138
01:04:39,614 --> 01:04:41,234
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

1139
01:04:41,944 --> 01:04:43,954
Ayuk! A waterfall.

1140
01:04:44,784 --> 01:04:46,074
Waterfall!

1141
01:04:46,164 --> 01:04:48,454
(BOTH GASP)

1142
01:04:51,164 --> 01:04:53,664
(BOTH YELL)

1143
01:04:56,334 --> 01:04:58,424
Dad!

1144
01:04:58,504 --> 01:04:59,634
Max!

1145
01:05:04,384 --> 01:05:07,394
(GRUNTS, COUGHS)

1146
01:05:14,774 --> 01:05:16,564
Grab ahold, Max!

1147
01:05:17,194 --> 01:05:18,314
(GRUNTS)

1148
01:05:22,324 --> 01:05:23,994
-No!
-(GASPS)

1149
01:05:24,074 --> 01:05:25,994
No! Ah! (GASPS)

1150
01:05:29,074 --> 01:05:30,164
(GRUNTS)

1151
01:05:30,244 --> 01:05:31,994
Whoa!

1152
01:05:32,834 --> 01:05:34,584
(GASPS IN FEAR)

1153
01:05:37,044 --> 01:05:38,794
(CRIES OUT)

1154
01:05:38,884 --> 01:05:41,634
Aaaaaaaaaah!

1155
01:05:45,304 --> 01:05:46,674
Dad!

1156
01:05:47,434 --> 01:05:48,514
(GRUNTS)

1157
01:05:58,484 --> 01:05:59,854
Aaaaaaah!

1158
01:06:00,814 --> 01:06:03,574
Ten o'clock, two o'clock,
quarter to three. Tour jeté.

1159
01:06:03,654 --> 01:06:04,944
Twist. I'm a little teapot

1160
01:06:05,034 --> 01:06:06,444
Let her fly!

1161
01:06:06,534 --> 01:06:08,454
(GOOFY SCREAMS)

1162
01:06:14,334 --> 01:06:15,914
Huh? (GRUNTS)

1163
01:06:16,004 --> 01:06:18,214
Aaah! Aah! Aah!

1164
01:06:18,294 --> 01:06:19,424
(STRAINED GRUNTING)

1165
01:06:22,544 --> 01:06:24,464
(RELIEVED CHUCKLE)

1166
01:06:34,184 --> 01:06:35,774
(RELIEVED SIGH)

1167
01:06:35,854 --> 01:06:37,894
The perfect cast.

1168
01:06:54,834 --> 01:06:57,874
Boy, this has been one crazy vacation.

1169
01:06:57,954 --> 01:06:59,874
And it's not over yet!

1170
01:07:05,674 --> 01:07:08,344
-(RIOTOUS CHEERING)
-(ROCK MUSIC PLAYS)

1171
01:07:12,684 --> 01:07:14,224
(THUDS)

1172
01:07:19,354 --> 01:07:20,354
-(WHISPERS) Dad.
-(SONG BEGINS)

1173
01:07:20,434 --> 01:07:23,274
Oof. We made it!

1174
01:07:23,354 --> 01:07:25,404
Come on, Max. Let's get you onstage.

1175
01:07:25,484 --> 01:07:27,194
Uh, maybe this isn't such a good idea.

1176
01:07:27,284 --> 01:07:30,074
(SINGING) Yeah, yeah

1177
01:07:30,154 --> 01:07:31,534
Oh, then again...

1178
01:07:32,414 --> 01:07:34,574
Dad? Dad!

1179
01:07:34,664 --> 01:07:36,494
POWERLINE: (SINGING) Heyyeah

1180
01:07:37,994 --> 01:07:42,624
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLES)

1181
01:07:42,754 --> 01:07:45,084
(SINGS) I got myself a notion

1182
01:07:45,174 --> 01:07:46,594
(CROWD CHEERS)

1183
01:07:46,674 --> 01:07:49,714
One I know that you'll understand

1184
01:07:49,804 --> 01:07:52,724
We set the world in motion

1185
01:07:53,304 --> 01:07:57,354
By reaching out for each other's hand

1186
01:07:57,434 --> 01:07:59,274
-Dad?
-Maybe we'll discover

1187
01:07:59,354 --> 01:08:01,894
What we should have known all along

1188
01:08:01,984 --> 01:08:03,854
-What are you doin' here? Hey!
-Yeah

1189
01:08:04,814 --> 01:08:06,734
-One way or another
-Max? Max?

1190
01:08:06,814 --> 01:08:09,784
-Together's where we both belong
-(SCREAMS)

1191
01:08:09,864 --> 01:08:14,034
If we listen to each other's heart

1192
01:08:14,114 --> 01:08:17,124
We'll find we're never too far apart

1193
01:08:17,204 --> 01:08:20,834
And maybe love is the reason why

1194
01:08:20,914 --> 01:08:22,874
For the first time ever

1195
01:08:22,964 --> 01:08:25,674
We're seein' it I-2-I

1196
01:08:25,754 --> 01:08:27,504
That Goof kid ain't there.

1197
01:08:28,424 --> 01:08:30,134
Don't worry, he'll be there.

1198
01:08:30,764 --> 01:08:34,344
-Seein' it I-2-I
-(GRUNTS)

1199
01:08:34,434 --> 01:08:36,594
Seein' it I-2-I

1200
01:08:36,684 --> 01:08:38,894
Excuse me. Uh...

1201
01:08:38,974 --> 01:08:41,354
Seein' it I-2-I

1202
01:08:41,434 --> 01:08:43,774
-I think we're seein' it
-Max?

1203
01:08:43,854 --> 01:08:45,944
Yeow-ee! Yeow-ee!

1204
01:08:46,694 --> 01:08:48,064
(YOWLS)

1205
01:08:51,324 --> 01:08:52,494
Hey, Dad. Dad!

1206
01:08:52,574 --> 01:08:54,204
Do the perfect cast!

1207
01:08:56,824 --> 01:08:58,284
(CROWD CHEERS)

1208
01:09:01,124 --> 01:09:03,254
If you're ever lonely

1209
01:09:03,334 --> 01:09:06,464
Stop, you don't have to be

1210
01:09:06,544 --> 01:09:09,214
Whoa! Whoaaa!

1211
01:09:09,294 --> 01:09:12,094
After all, it's only a beat away

1212
01:09:12,174 --> 01:09:14,804
From you to me

1213
01:09:14,884 --> 01:09:17,974
-Take a look inside to see
-Yeah

1214
01:09:18,054 --> 01:09:22,264
If we listen to each other's heart

1215
01:09:22,354 --> 01:09:26,854
Yeah! Max is on the tube!
That's Max. I know him...

1216
01:09:26,944 --> 01:09:29,194
And maybe love is the reason why

1217
01:09:29,274 --> 01:09:32,074
For the first time ever
We're seein' it I-2-I

1218
01:09:32,154 --> 01:09:34,744
-He did it!
-(CHOKES, COUGHS)

1219
01:09:35,324 --> 01:09:37,664
Seein' it I-2-I

1220
01:09:37,744 --> 01:09:40,204
Seein' it I-2-I, baby

1221
01:09:40,284 --> 01:09:46,214
-WOMAN: For the first time
-For the first time

1222
01:09:48,004 --> 01:09:51,214
-Seein' it, seein' it, baby
-Yeah!

1223
01:09:51,294 --> 01:09:53,504
-Yeah, yeah
-(LAUGHS)

1224
01:09:53,594 --> 01:09:57,224
For the first time ever, yeah, yeah, yeah

1225
01:09:57,304 --> 01:09:58,684
Come on, baby

1226
01:09:58,764 --> 01:10:02,304
-I-2-I
-I-2-I

1227
01:10:02,394 --> 01:10:06,354
I-2-I

1228
01:10:06,434 --> 01:10:09,904
Yeah, I-2-I

1229
01:10:09,984 --> 01:10:13,444
(CROWD CHEERS)

1230
01:10:13,524 --> 01:10:15,864
(CAR ENGINE SPUTTERS)

1231
01:10:17,744 --> 01:10:19,534
(CAR BACKFIRES)

1232
01:10:19,614 --> 01:10:20,874
(CLANGS)

1233
01:10:22,534 --> 01:10:24,494
You're doin' the right thing, son.

1234
01:10:24,584 --> 01:10:26,164
Yeah, I know.

1235
01:10:26,254 --> 01:10:29,004
But she'll probably
never talk to me again.

1236
01:10:29,084 --> 01:10:31,254
Well, if she doesn't...

1237
01:10:31,334 --> 01:10:33,844
maybe she's just not the one for you.

1238
01:10:35,634 --> 01:10:37,134
That's what I'm afraid of.

1239
01:10:49,814 --> 01:10:51,154
(DEEP SIGH)

1240
01:10:52,814 --> 01:10:54,324
(DOORBELL RINGS)

1241
01:10:54,404 --> 01:10:56,574
(DOOR OPENS)

1242
01:10:56,654 --> 01:10:59,154
(GROWLS)

1243
01:10:59,244 --> 01:11:01,284
